to the editor re an end at last to the battle of concorde by clyde haberman nyc column oct 24 the most amazing and magical sight while i was windsurfing at sheepshead bay was when among the terns and gulls the concorde would majestically appear at a slow subsonic speed on its way to land at kennedy international airport i still remember some years ago when sailing on a perfectly clear day i happened onto a perfect tack the alignment with a northerly view of the lowlands of brooklyn with the manhattan skyline in the distance and with the concorde flying directly overhead it was for sure a kodak moment w derman brooklyn oct 24 2003

